Pang: Gyaaahh!
Hestia: What's happening? Pang seems to be in a lot of pain.
Jia-Shen: Oh, I know!
Jia-Shen: Puggi, do you still have that thing I gave ya?
Puggi: Hm? You mean... this?
Jia-Shen: Yeah, that! Quick, use it on Pang!
Puggi: Alright~ Here goes!!
Pang: Wah... wahh...
Pang: Wah... Have I lost again?
Nightmare Pang: Admit it, you say you want to stop him, but are you sure you understand your intentions?
Pang: Yao is my comrade, that's exactly why I need to stop him!!
Nightmare Pang: Then why do you fight with such reserve?
Pang: Because...
Nightmare Pang: Fight or not? Kill or not? Start... stop... start... stop...
Nightmare Pang: You say you want it, but when it's right in front of you... you run away! You want to look innocent, so you don't spill blood.
Pang: T-That's not true at all...
Nightmare Pang: You don't think and you don't act! Some day, everyone's going to die from your inaction!
Nightmare Pang: Then you'll finally face the truth!
Pang: No!!!
Pang: I know... I know I can't save him...
Yan-Bo: With would you do with an apple, rotten to the core?
Pang: ...I'd throw it out, of course.
Yan-Bo: That's right. Dispose of it, let rotten fruit return to the earth.
Pang: ...And let the seeds bear fruit once again. Death begets life...
Pang: Begone, foul nightmare! Begone, nagging regrets!!
Nightmare Pang: It's no use, you'll just keep making the same mistakes.
Pang: And if I do, I'll strike you down again!
Puggi: Hey you, you're finally awake!
Pang: Puggi? Hestia? Jia-Shen?
Hestia: Yay! We thought you'd never wake up...
Pang: ...I'm sorry to worry you all.
Jia-Shen: Does anything hurt? Are you alright?
Pang: I'm fine, I just... feel strange.
Jia-Shen: Maybe it's just after-effects of the skybranch.
Pang: H-Hold on, did you say skybranch!? Then, that means I was just...!
Puggi: Hehehe, you were making some real funny faces!
Jia-Shen: Well, at least the skybranch had an effect on him.
Pang: Oh, right... where's Yao!?
Jia-Shen: Ah, um...
Pang: I need to stop him!
Jia-Shen: But yer hurt, Pang!
Pang: It doesn't matter.
Hestia: He'll go anyway.
Puggi: That's my little bro! I know you can send that punk flying with a flick of your wrist!
Puggi: So, you'll go deal with him and be right back, right?
Pang: Yes... I'll be right back.
Tapir Protector: Hold, everybody! His wounds are deep, he shouldn't last much longer!
Yao: Such loyalty... wasted on corruption.
Pang: That may be so, but then you were also born out of such corruption!
Pang: The Alliance may be unjust, I'll give you that... But it has much beauty, if you look hard enough.
Yao: Hmph, more naive drivel. The Alliance should be glad it has such blind followers.
Pang: Enough, Yao! The Alliance... the Tiger Tribe... none of it matters!
Pang: I protect my friends from their enemies, no matter who they are or where they're from... Even if that enemy is you!
Yao: Protect!? Hah! With what, that weak punch of yours?
Pang: Want to try that weak punch again?
Yao: Hmph... Best friends make the worst enemies.
Yao: Come, try and stop me! I won't go easy on you!
Yao: Die!
Pang: Gagh... gungh... Yao...
Yao: Remember those days we used to spar? You'd always lose, and I always thought you were letting me win...
Pang: ...The past is past.
Yao: Yes, things are different now.
Yao: Your skills have improved.
Pang: Hmph... You're already hurt. Otherwise, I might not have won.
Yao: Our wounds have simply put us on equal footing.
Yao: That said...
Yao: You may have broken my body, but my ideals remain ever steadfast!
Yao: Listen... I know some of my actions may not have been righteous, but... But the Alliance is even worse!
Yao: I couldn't simply sit back and shut up. I needed to... fight back...
Pang: No! Gyaah!
Yao: Even if I didn't win the fight, at least I...
Chiyuki: My savior...
Yao: I don't need to... fight any longer!
Pang: It was you!
Chiyuki: Don't!!
Chiyuki: Sa... vior...
Pang: That's...
